headline: Does BMY's AI Collaboration With insitro Signal a New Growth Path in Neuroscience?
summary: On October 14, insitro and Bristol-Myers Squibb announced an extension of their collaboration to accelerate AI-driven discovery of novel small molecule therapies for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), leveraging insitro’s ChemML™ platform and up to US$20 million in new funding for the next phase. If successful, the partnership could lead to milestone payments of over US$2 billion to insitro and further establish the role of advanced machine learning in tackling difficult neurological...

headline: NeoGenomics (NEO) Moves 6.3% Higher: Will This Strength Last?
